LogFile.FinalText: It's amazing how they look alike. That is what many Danes think about Denmark's two princesses. There are many similarities between Mary and Marie, but just as many, if not more, dissimilarities. They both come from countries outside Denmark, none of them are born into royalty, and each of them have found a Danish prince. Mary is married to crownprince Frederik and Marie is married to Prince Joachim. Even their names and their looks are very similar. Both of them are extraordinary beauties with long dark hair and big brown eyes. But despite the many similarities, Mary and Marie are also two independent individuals who have lived and are still living different lifes, which influences their values and personalities in different ways.
